    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><note>Il <rs key="#Princeps">principe</rs>
                            <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/303">Arechi II</persName> offre
                            al monastero di S. Sofia di <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/110"
                                >Benevento</placeName> (prosegue l'elenco iniziato con il doc.
                            3535):</note></ab> <ab>(…) [26] Nec non et in <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Villages/settlements #Cows #Fiscal_property #Slave"
                            ref="#places/3418"><geogName ref="#estates/3404"
                                key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldato
                            Bifernensi</geogName></placeName> concessimus <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants"
                            >cortisanos</rs>, hi sunt <name ref="Iohannes">Iohannem</name> et <name
                            ref="Walterius">Vvaltari</name> cum uxoribus et filiis suis et omnibus
                        sibi pertinentibus, seu et unam sororem <name ref="Indari">Indari</name>,
                        hos autem cum integra portione eorum <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/85"
                            >Sancte Sophie monasterio</orgName> concessimus possidendum. Item et in
                        eodem <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldato</rs> concessimus <rs
                            key="#Cows #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Slave_labour"
                            >baccarios</rs>, hi sunt <name ref="Grausus">Grauso</name> cum uxore et
                        filiis seu et noras et nepotes eius et omnia eis pertinentia, nec non et
                            <name ref="Sindo">Sindonem</name> cum uxore et filiis suis seu et <rs
                            key="#Cows">baccas</rs> in integrum, qui fuerunt <rs key="#Slave"
                            >servi</rs>
                        <name ref="Rimichi">Rimichis</name> et de germano eius <rs
                            key="#Specialized_workers">carpentarii</rs> nostri. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
